## [Conventional Commits](https://docs.fdnd.nl/conventies.html#conventional-commits)

### How to write a conventional commit
To be sure what type of commit you'll write you need to know the[ types of commits](https://docs.fdnd.nl/conventies.html#allowed-commit-types). If you know which type of commit this is you'll be able to write a commit message yourself. For this example i'll be writing a fix I made for color:

```
title: fix: #1532 Color support (Header)

message: For better support in older browsers I used the Supports query 
and the media prefers-color-scheme query to have it work for older and newer generations.
```

To break it down: 
title: (type of commit): (issue you've worked on) (descriptive title) ( (The page or component you've worked on) ) 
message: (summary of what you've been working on in this commit)
